Movie Explorer

Movie Explorer is a web application that allows users to browse, search, and manage a collection of movies. It demonstrates JavaScript concepts such as handling events, manipulating the DOM, and communicating with a server using GET, POST, PATCH, and DELETE requests.

Features

Fetch and display movie details from a local JSON server.

Search for movies by title.

View movie descriptions, ratings, and available tickets.

Purchase tickets and update availability.

Add new movies to the collection.

Delete movies from the database.

Technologies Used

HTML

CSS

JavaScript

JSON Server (Mock Backend)

Setup Instructions

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/elizabeth-7664/movie-explorer.git

Navigate into the project directory:

cd movie-explorer

Install dependencies (if needed):

npm install

Start the JSON Server:

json-server --watch db.json

Open index.html in your browser to interact with the application.

API Endpoints

The application interacts with the following API endpoints:

GET /movies - Retrieves a list of movies.

GET /movies/:id - Retrieves details of a specific movie.

PATCH /movies/:id - Updates movie details (e.g., available tickets).

POST /movies - Adds a new movie to the collection.

DELETE /movies/:id - Removes a movie from the database.

How to Use

Search for a movie by typing its title in the search bar.

Select a movie from the list to view its details.

Click the "Buy Ticket" button to reduce the available ticket count.

If tickets are sold out, the button will be disabled.

Add new movies using the provided form.

Delete a movie from the list if necessary.

